				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the point that some people are trying to make is this:
<br />

<br />
Quillmane can drop Cloak or Legs
<br />
Fabled Quillmane can drop Fabled Cloak or Cloak or Legs
<br />

<br />
Quillmane is still on her own very rare timer, while the Fabled, being part of the celebration is on a more common (yet still rare) spawn cycle.
<br />

<br />
The Fabled doesnt hurt your chance on the epic drop, but gives you added chances to get the needed Cloak for the Epic.
<br />

<br />
You just happened to get the Fabled Cloak, in the RNG process.  Be thankful that you have a chance to get the Epic Drop at an increased rate compared to prior to the existence of the Fabled.  Once the Fabled is gone, we'll be back to a much longer wait for the RNG to give us a Cloak.
<br />

<br />
This isnt a knock at your request, but I dont see how you could possibly feel you deserve an exchange, when you have no grounds to complain about getting the wrong drop from a mob that has a random loot table.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=673488&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Rhezor Rhektor (Cleric)</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=932563&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fazena (Magician)</a>
