			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem is the Fable Cloak drops every single time the Fabled Quil is killed. 
<br />

<br />
The normal cloak and leggings also have a chance to drop.
<br />

<br />
The Fable Cloak is not on the same loot table as the normal cloak.  IE you can get a fabled and normal cloak from same Fabled Quil.
<br />

<br />
My bet is Fabled IS on same spawn table as normal just like in the other areas.  I know for a fact Fabled Drelzna, normal Drelzna are on same table.  In Najena you have a chance at either a necromancer or normal Drelzna or Fabled Drelzna spawning. I'd be very surprised that quilmane isn't the same way.
<br />

<br />
The influx of cloaks on servers I'm thinking has nothing to do with faster spawn times of Quilmane but rather the simple fact tons of people are hunting him now.  Before it was just some mob to get if you happen to be in SK when it spawned(or were PLing someone at the spires).
<br />

<br />
The Fabled Cloak should NOT be allowed to be turned in for the Mage Epic.  It wasn't put in the game for that but for purely historical reasons.  All the Fabled were made to celebrate 5 years of EQ.  Plain and Simple.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.spiderstomper.net" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.spiderstomper.net/mantria.jpg" border="0" /></a>
